tool.name: GDVSpectra_Likelihood

param.name: in_nc_file
param.dialogReference:
A raw satellite data NetCDF generated by the COG Fetch module. Requires x, y, time and satellite band variables.

Note: three or more years is required to perform GDV Likelihood modelling.

param.name: out_likelihood_nc_file
param.dialogReference: The folder location and filename of the output NetCDF file containing GDV Likelihood map data.

param.name: in_wet_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) which best represent the wettest period of the study area region.

The wet and dry months are used to generate vegetation and moisture stability across years. Two or more months recommended to ensure data is available for the analysis.

param.name: in_dry_months
param.dialogReference:
The month(s) which best represent the driest period of the study area region.

The wet and dry months are used to generate vegetation and moisture stability across years. Two or more months recommended to ensure data is available for the analysis.

param.name: in_veg_idx
param.expression: MAVI | NDVI | EVI | SAVI | MSAVI | SLAVI | kNDVI | TCG
param.dialogReference:
The vegetation index in which to represent vegetation greenness within the study area. The following vegetation indices are available:

- NDVI (Normalized Difference Vegetation Index)

- EVI (Enhanced Vegetation Index)

- SAVI (Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- MSAVI (Modified Soil-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- SLAVI (Specific Leaf Area Vegetation Index)

- MAVI (Moisture-Adjusted Vegetation Index)

- kNDVI (Non-linear Normalized Vegetation Index)

- TCG (Tasselled Cap Greenness)

The default index is set to MAVI, which performs well in the Pilbara region of Western Australia.

param.name: in_mst_idx
param.dialogReference:
The moisture index in which to represent vegetation moisture within the study area. The following vegetation indices are available:

- NDMI (Normalized Difference Moisture Index)

- GVMI (Global Vegetation Moisture Index)

The default index is set to NDMI, which performs well in the Pilbara region of Western Australia.

param.name: in_zscore_pvalue
param.dialogReference:
The p-value used to test the significance of an outlier in a Z-Test. This is used to drive outlier removal and can be helpful to remove cloud pixels that were not captured by the DEA Fmask.

The lower the p-value, the more significant (or extreme) a value must deviate from the population sample in order to be removed.

No p-value is the default. This ensures no outlier removal is performed.

param.name: in_stand_qupper
param.dialogReference:
The upper n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values. Used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the maximum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_stand_qlower
param.dialogReference:
The lower n percentile of the vegetation and moisture index values. Used during invariant target standardisation and rescaling. The percentile is used as the minimum is prone to severe outliers.

The default value is recommended as it typically produces optimal results.

param.name: in_fmask_flags
param.expression: NoData | Valid | Cloud | Shadow | Snow | Water
param.dialogReference:
Classes captured within the OA measurement band provided for each satellite image via the DEA Fmask algorithm.

Only the selected pixel classes will be returned, whilst all others will be set to NoData (i.e., masked out).

param.name: in_max_cloud
param.dialogReference:
The maximum percentage of cloud cover existing per satellite image before it is discarded from analysis.

A value of 0 will return all satellite data with no cloud cover. A value of 10 will discard all satellite data with 11% or more cloud presence. A value of 100 will return all images regardless.

param.name: in_interpolate
param.dialogReference:
Whether to interpolate erroneous pixels that are masked out via the Mask band.

If checked, linear interpolation is applied along the time dimension of the input NetCDF, and missing pixels are filled.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the results to the currently active map once modelling is complete or not.

tool.summary:
Generates groundwater dependent vegetation (GDV) likelihood maps based on a spatial multicriteria evaluation (SMCE) approach. This approach detects potential GDV via a time series of vegetation indices, moisture indices and seasonal stability. These variables are weighted and combined via an Analytical Hierarchy Process (AHP), resulting in a single GDV likelihood (probability) map for every year provided within an input satellite data NetCDF file.
